Cell.Text: [S] I warned them. I knew something like this would happen eventually. But they didn't listen, and look where it's gotten them. | This attack... it's unlike the vampires. Do we at least know what they were after, or is this completely a lost cause?
None of this makes any sense. What does she have to do with this?

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranVQ02Response1Topic: They were trying to free a woman trapped in a crypt.

Cell.Text: None of this feels right. We need to know more.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranVQ02SeranaHome1: She just wants to go home.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Well, it seems the Dawnguard really is needed again. | While I ready things here, you find out what this woman means to the vampires. She must be important somehow. | I'll admit, I don't know that I can trust you, but I know I can't rely on the Vigilants for anything. So we'll have to work together for now. | If you can prove you're reliable, maybe you can join the Dawnguard. We have ways of dealing with vampires.
Why her? What significance does she have? We don't have enough information.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranVQ02SeranaHome2: I don't know, but she must be connected.

Cell.Text: It certainly seems the Vigilants of Stendarr can't help themselves. No surprise there.
Well, I certainly can't help any less than the Vigilants of Stendarr, now can I?
[S] And I suppose you're the one Tolan says is actually doing something about this mess. | These Vigilants are nothing but talk.

Right to the point, aren't you. I like that. Not like those fools in the order. | We should keep it small. Too many people, and we'll draw unwanted attention to ourselves. | I think we'll want Sorine Jurard. Breton girl, whip-smart and good with tinkering. Fascination with the Dwemer. Weapons in particular. | Last I knew, she was out in the Reach, convinced she was about to find the biggest dwarven ruins yet.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranIntroWhoPeopleTopic: Where can I find the people we need?

Cell.Text: Might need a little convincing, but she should.

[S] You'll also want to find Gunmar. Big brute of a Nord, hates vampires almost as much as I do. | Got it into his head years back that his experience with animals would help. Trolls in particular, from what I hear. | Last I knew he was out scouring Skyrim for more beasts to tame. | Bring the two of them back here, and we can get started on coming up with a plan.
Do we at least know what the vampires are after?
And so we've delivered her right to them. I should've kept her here until we were certain...

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranS20VampireInfo1: The woman was a vampire, and they've been looking for her.

Cell.Text: They what? | By the Divines, this couldn't get much worse. This is more than you and I can handle.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranS20VampireInfo2: They also have an Elder Scroll.

Cell.Text: When did I say that? | We just need... we need help.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranIntroFinalResponse1: So you're just going to give up?

Cell.Text: [S] If they're bold enough to attack us here, then this may be bigger than I thought. I have good men here, but... | There are people I've met and worked with over the years. We need their skills, their talents, if we're going to survive this. | If you can find them, we might have a chance.
Well of course we do. I'm old, not stupid. | We're going to need some help.

Look at this. I should've known it was a mistake letting the Vigilants in here. | I've allowed Tolan to stay here for now, but the rest of the Vigilants can fend for themselves. | I don't suppose you have some good news for me.
Damn. Well what do you know?
Of course. Why did I suppose differently. Fine, tell me what you know.

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranS20Response2: I have news, but I wouldn't call it good.

Cell.Text: What is this place?

<<Shared>> This wonderful hideout is Fort Dawnguard. | Originally owned by the Jarl of Riften back in the Second Era, it was a bit of a black mark on the Hold's history. | I'm trying to put it to good use.

Isn't it obvious? They're soft, the lot of them. | Totally unprepared for any real threat. And yet I was the one ridiculed for trying to be ready for anything. | "Too extreme", they called me. Well, that doesn't seem to have worked out in their favor, now has it?

Node.Caption: DLC1HunterBaseIntroIsranVigilantBeefTopic: What do you have against the Vigilants?

Cell.Text: Vampires need to be dealt with. Hunted, rooted out, destroyed. | Once there was a group dedicated to a similar cause. They called themselves the Dawnguard. | They're gone now, but the idea was, and is, a good one. I intend to do something about it. | This latest attack proves it's the right time.
